reviews.review_text:
Seeing the dead at the Tower.... f all you people, so jealous. I can just imagine the balcony shaking so hard from Phil bombs that a handful of spunions ran for cover each night. 

1st and foremost, Top 10 all time Help>Slip>Franklin's...HANDS DOWN.

The Dancin is a party all the way, and the whole show is just really strong. But this matrix...oh this matrix, it's fantastic. It has a handful of unimportant bumps, otherwise stellar, and easily the best source of this show around. Definitely one of those that you need to get because having any other source as your go to in the collection automatically drops it a full letter grade. Way to go Tobin. 

Playing: 8.5/10
Sound: 9.6/10
Overall: 9/10

Strange Matrix Playing is pretty tight and the matrix always adds a nice feeling but this one seems to be out of sync at times and the echo can cause a mild flashback if your not careful... Overall good show with some weak patch work. The re-dubbing of AUD clips sounds really strange and takes away from the overall sound quality. 4 Star show with 3 Star mix. Always thankful for the hard work everyone does with these matrix mixes so worth a listen if you like 76' Dead

Peace
  Gagas
